description: Load when the task involves branch naming, commit messages, MR/Jira wording, or validation flow — i.e. anything that touches `conductor` outputs
---

This rule supplies the conventions enforced across every `conductor` output
(branch / commit / MR body / Jira comment / recap). The canonical source is
`.conductor/CONVENTIONS.md`; this rule is a **summary** for quick reference.

## Branch & commit

- Branch: `{type}/{ISSUE_KEY}-{kebab-slug}` where `type` is derived from
  issue type via `branch.prefix_map` in `.conductor/workflow.yml`
  (e.g. Bug → `fix`, Task / Story → `feat`, Improvement → `refactor`,
  Documentation → `docs`).
- Commit subject: `{type}: {ISSUE_KEY} <한국어 주제>`. One-line body
  optional. The CLI renders this from `commit-message.md` — do not invent
  your own format.

## Validation

- Static checks: whatever `workflow.yml > validation.static` lists.
  Typically `pnpm run lint`, `pnpm run type-check`, and `vitest related`
  against changed files (not the whole suite — CI covers global regression).
- Run them via the CLI, not by hand, so results land in `.work/{KEY}.md`.

## MR & Jira wording

- MR title: `{type}: {ISSUE_KEY} <subject>` (Jira key included for auto-link).
- MR body: rendered from `mr-template.md`. Required sections: 📝 변경 요약,
  📂 변경 파일, ✅ 자동 검증, 🧪 테스트 방법, 📸 스크린샷, 👤 Authorship.
- Jira ship comment: `jira-comment-ship.md`. Always includes MR URL and
  authorship footer.

## Authorship footer

All artifacts end with:

```
Generated via `conductor {COMMAND}` — agent Cursor · conductor-kit v{CLI_VERSION} · user {USER}
```

The `Cursor` label is hardcoded in `.cursor/commands/conductor-*.md`.

## Files you should not touch directly

- `.work/{KEY}.md` status lines — CLI-owned.
- Generated type files (e.g. `src/types/api/APIs.ts` if it exists) —
  regenerated from OpenAPI.
- `node_modules/`, `pnpm-lock.yaml`, `package.json` dependency fields —
  discuss before edits.
